    "title": {
        "rendered": "MatR: Bruce Springsteen, Bob Dylan, and Friends, Highway 61 Revisited"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>When Bob Dylan released\u00a0<em>Highway 61 Revisited\u00a0</em>in 1965, it was the first time he&#8217;d recorded with rock musicians&#8211;or really, with anything other than his guitar.</p>\n<p>So perhaps it&#8217;s fitting that each and every one of the five times Bruce performed the album&#8217;s title track was in the company of other notable musicians.</p>\n<p>From the very first time (two times, actually), performed in an ironically acoustic arrangement with Bonnie Raitt and Jackson Browne at the famous Christic shows in 1990&#8230;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2fQXHrG2INg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>(here&#8217;s a better audio version)</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/n6pxbliYc3Y?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8230;to the third time, with Dylan himself in 1994, when Bruce and Neil Young backed him on guitar during Dylan&#8217;s show at the Roseland Ballroom in New York City.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/l27EiQbgi54?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>A year later, Bruce performed a particularly hard rocking version in Berlin with Wolfgang Niedecken and his band.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WKI8yIG2oIE?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>And finally, during the encore of the very last Rising Tour show at Shea Stadium in 2003, Bruce played it with Dylan once again&#8211;this time with the E Street Band.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1ipSXZqyLGU?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Each performance featured a different arrangement; each outstanding in their own way.</p>\n<p>But: none of them had the whistle. IMO, that&#8217;s the secret ingredient that made the original so much fun.</p>\n<p>Just saying.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8hr3Stnk8_k?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Highway 61 Revisited<br />\n</strong><strong>First performed:\u00a0</strong>November 16, 1990 (Los Angeles, CA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:\u00a0</strong>October 4, 2003 (New York City, NY)</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>When Bruce covers &#8220;Highway 61 Revisited,&#8221; it&#8217;s always a group effort. Watch and listen to all four team-ups on Dylan&#8217;s classic rocker.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
